-- ACS, Banesto, Iberdrola, Santander May Be Active: Iberian Equity Preview
-- Emma Ross-Thomas
-- 2010-07-12T06:43:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/acs-banesto-iberdrola-santander-may-be-active-iberian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spain and Portugal trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close.  
 Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  rose 0.5 percent to 10,127.30.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index  fell 1.7 percent to 7,317.93.  
 Spanish stocks:  
 Actividades de Construccion & Servicios SA  (ACS SM): Spain
won’t award contracts for new public-works projects until 2016,
El Mundo reported, citing unidentified people who attended a
meeting with Deputy Minister for Infrastructure  Victor Morlan .
The construction company’s shares fell 30 cents, or 0.9 percent,
to 32.20 euros.  
 Banco Espanol de Credito SA  (BTO SM): Banesto,  Bankinter SA 
(BKT SM) and  Banco Pastor SA  (PAS SM) may need to raise 1.16
billion euros ($1.47 billion) in capital to cope with potential
losses under a “stressed” scenario, El Economista reported,
citing estimates by JPMorgan Chase & Co. Banesto shares fell 0.2
percent, Bankinter fell 0.9 percent and Banco Pastor declined
0.7 percent.  
 Banco Popular Espanol SA  (POP SM):  Angel Ron , the chairman
of Spain’s third-largest bank, sees “no reason to think”
stress tests will go badly, El Mundo reported, citing an
interview. The shares fell 0.1 percent to 4.78 euros.  
 Banco Santander SA  (SAN SM): Spain’s largest bank aims to
increase its 10 percent market share in Latin America by two or
three percentage points, Latin American head  Francisco Luzon 
told Expansion in an interview. The bank isn’t in talks to buy
assets or capacity in Spain, Luzon also said. The shares gained
2 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 9.97 euros.  
 Ferrovial SA  (FER SM): BAA Ltd.’s U.K. airports handled 9.5
million passengers last month, a decrease of 1.7 percent from a
year earlier, the company said in a Regulatory News Service
statement today. Shares in Ferrovial, owner of BAA, advanced 13
cents, or 2.3 percent, to 5.80 euros.  
 Iberdrola SA  (IBE SM): A court rejected a request by
Actividades de Construccion & Servicios SA to suspend a decision
by Iberdrola shareholders that blocked the builder from the
power company’s board, Cinco Dias reported. Iberdrola shares
rose 3 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 5.16 euros.  
      Repsol YPF SA  (REP SM) Spain’s largest oil company
increased its estimate for oil reserves in Spain to 6.8 million
barrels from 2.4 million barrels in 2008, El Pais reported,
citing a U.S. regulatory filing. The shares gained 34 cents, or
2 percent, to 17.59 euros.  
